{"type":"message","id":"1f4381fd","parentId":"dd04ce58","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:23:41.208Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zwq0qnvyek6e_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4837\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='a' new_len=0\r\n[master 5af8f12] pulse: 2026-03-24 132316\n 5 files changed, 217 insertions(+), 63 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 132316.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 132216.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 132316 - The CFI compression synthesis identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and derived a three-dimensional filter. The next logical step is implementing and testing Strategy C: hybrid CFIxFreq scoring to distinguish true research trajectory tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-breeze","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4837\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='a' new_len=0\r\n[master 5af8f12] pulse: 2026-03-24 132316\n 5 files changed, 217 insertions(+), 63 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 132316.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 132216.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 132316 - The CFI compression synthesis identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and derived a three-dimensional filter. The next logical step is implementing and testing Strategy C: hybrid CFIxFreq scoring to distinguish true research trajectory tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n","name":"pwsh C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774373021204}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd59b571","parentId":"1f4381fd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:23:41.211Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zwq0qnvyek6e_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 132216\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state based on the provided context:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment was just completed with key findings:\r\n   - CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n   - Constant Format Problem identified - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n   - Three-dimensional filter needed: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring\r\n\r\n3. The pending action is: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nSo I should implement the next step in the compression research. The current pulse analysis was done in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Look at the current pulse data or create the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Implement Strategy C: CFI × min(1, freq/120) scoring\r\n\r\nLet me check what needs to be done. The key insight is:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to run the next experiment to test this hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions:\r\n- \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nThis suggests I should create a new experiment file or modify the existing analysis to implement Strategy C.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script for Strategy C\r\n2. Update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the new experiment plan\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a \"stateless discontinuous agent\" and need to advance the goals, the most concrete next step would be to create a new experiment file for Strategy C that implements the hybrid scoring.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new file: `research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` that outlines the experiment design for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that binary thresholds fail due to the constant-format problem. Strategy C (hybrid scoring) is the logical next step to distinguish true research tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experiment specification for Strategy C hybrid scoring, implementing the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This will test if the continuous scoring function can cleanly separate research trajectories from constant-format tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n**Objective:** Test continuous scoring function vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n### Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score | Expected |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|----------|\r\n| Research trajectory (\"Phase 1\") | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96×1.0=0.96 | KEEP |\r\n| True causal (freq<120) | 60 | 0.7 | 0.7×0.5=0.35 | KEEP |\r\n| Constant format (\"for next\") | 160 | 1.0 | 1.0×1.0=1.0 | PENALIZE |\r\n| Rare signal (freq=3) | 3 | 0.8 | 0.8×0.025=0.02 | DROP |\r\n\r\n### Key Insight\r\nThe penalty term `min(1, freq/120)` naturally downweights tokens at freq>120 without a hard cutoff.\r\n\r\n### Testable Hypotheses\r\n1. **H1:** score > 0.3 distinguishes research tokens from noise (precision test)\r\n2. **H2:** Tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.0 score < 0.5 when freq penalty applies (constant format detection)\r\n3. **H3:** The scoring curve is smooth across the freq spectrum\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n- Generate scores for all tokens in pulse corpus\r\n- Plot score vs freq for CFI ≥ 0.5 tokens\r\n- Identify optimal threshold via precision/recall on labeled research tokens\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Experiment designed\r\n- [ ] Implementation coded\r\n- [ ] Results analyzed\r\n- [ ] Threshold validated\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:22:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774373021208}}
